body.description: No more frustration trying to find your lost pacifiers at night! This pacifier glows in the dark, making it easy for baby and parent to find in the evening hours. Specially designed with your little one’s teeth and jaw in mind, the MAM Perfect Pacifier is clinically proven* to reduce the risk of open bite and increased overbite later in life. With a 60% thinner neck and 4 times more flexible nipple** than a regular pacifier, you can be assured that your little one’s favorite binky is safe for their development as it puts less pressure on their jaw and teeth. MAM’s medically engineered nipples feature life-like, SkinSoft textured silicone that feels more natural, just like mom. With multiple nipple and shield sizes to pick from, MAM nipples are easily accepted by babies of all ages, with 94% nipple acceptance among babies tested***. Babies simply love the ease and comfort of latching onto MAM nipples. Sterilize baby’s MAM pacifier in the microwave using the convenient MAM self-sterilizing storage case. Pacifiers kept in the closed box will remain disinfected for up to 48 hours: Fill pacifier case with water. Place pacifier in the pacifier case with the nipple facing down. Follow pacifier package instructions for microwave setting. Cool completely before use. *Y. Wagner, R. Heinrich-Weltzien, “Effect of a thinneck pacifier on primary dentition: a randomized controlled trial”, Orthodontics & Craniofacial Research, Volume 19, Issue 3, pages 127–136, August 2016. **Scientific reports from Wild Hi-Precision institute verify: the MAM Perfect’s teat neck is on average 60% thinner; test series by the University Clinic of Dentistry Vienna confirm: it is also on average 4 times more flexible than comparable pacifiers. (Between: 32% – 83% thinner / 1.1 – 19.5 times more flexible than regular silicone pacifiers). *** Market Research 2009-2017, tested with 1,508 babies. Please avoid leaving the pacifier in the sterilising solution for longer than the time recommended. Sometimes water may enter the inside of the nipple, this is because of a ventilation systems that exists in the nipple and helps make the pacifier orthodontic.

productInformation.name: Care instructions
productInformation.value: ‎Inspect carefully before each use. Pull the pacifier in all directions. Throw away at the first signs of damage or weakness. Only use dedicated pacifier holders tested to EN 12586. Never attach other ribbons or cords to a pacifier, your child may be strangled by them. Do not leave a pacifier in direct sunlight or near a source of heat or leave in sterilizing solution for longer than recommended, as this may weaken the nipple.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 1, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Ticks every box
reviews.reviewText: This is a 4th 2-pack in last 5 months that I am purchasing-unfortunately we keep loosing them so that’s why I keep buying more because I like to always have at least 3-4 handy that I leave in my daughters crib. They are very durable - my daughter has been teething non stop since 5 months and episodically she chews and bites her pacis-we haven’t had any issues to this day. Also I love that they glow in the dark and are very easy to locate at night time for the baby or me if I have to come into her room to soothe her. And additionally I have a peace of mind about the bite and those are the only pacis we have been using since 6 months when her first teeth came out. The storage/cleaning container is another great bonus-comes in handy for quick sterilization or for when we travel to nana or out of town

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent pacifier but...
reviews.reviewText: These are great, the night time, glow in the dark feature is amazing. You can find them as well as your baby. My issue is with the seller. What is pictured here is what I was expecting. This site didn't let me select any other graphic on the pacifier so I thought I was getting "Sweet Dreams" and the Star. Received something totally different but not worth sending back. Just the expectation wasn't met. Otherwise, great product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Glows in Dark, Cute design and helps babys teeth
reviews.reviewText: I love these pacifiers, love that they glow in the dark and not hard to find at night when baby needs it plus baby can find it himself. Cute design also and has helped with the teeth grow. Very flexible and not thick like other pacifiers. Iv always liked mams products and it's the only pacifier my baby will take, He's breastfed so is very picky. Iv tried numerous and he only takes this one. I recommend this to other mamas

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2020
reviews.reviewText: We are a mam pacifier using family, I love the cute design and it’s so awesome thy these are glow in the dark. My daughter has no trouble going from breastfeeding to using her pacifier at all. Only thing I would say I dislike is that when cleaning them/sterilizing them, it does get water trapped in the nipple part of the pacifier. Other than that we Absolutley love these, wouldn’t use anything else.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Didn't receive the ones pictured.
reviews.reviewText: I would give 5 stars but since I didn't receive the ones pictured, I'll give 4. Although it does mention that styles vary.. still I wanted the moon one. I got the set that comes with the one that says sweet dreams and the other with stars. It's still cute but the whole reason I purchased it was to get the moon pacifier. I'm a moon and stars fanatic but other then that I'm happy with it and so is my baby. I love that they glow in the dark. It makes life easier to be able to find the pacifier in the dark instead of having to turn on the light which wakes the baby then nobody sleeps. I also love that it comes with its own sterilizing case. I'm obsessed with the mam pacifiers. They have the coolest designs to choose from so your baby can be suckin in style. My son has at least 10 if them. They're great 💙

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I do like the design of the other MAM binkies that don't cover as much of the face, but this style nipple is definitely the best. I don't have to worry about it messing with my son's bite at all because of the thin base. For anyone worrying about how thin it is: when I threw away our old ones that were probably about 6 months old and well used, I tried them out. I bit it and pulled as hard as I could, and it barely even left a mark on the nipple. I definitely trust these binkies.
